-- Batista's OSX confirms filing for bankruptcy protection
-- 
-- Mon Nov 11, 2013 3:04pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/11/11/us-brazil-batista-osx-filing-idUSBRE9AA0W820131111

 

 RIO DE JANEIRO  (Reuters) - OSX Brasil SA, the Brazilian shipbuilder controlled by former billionaire Eike Batista, filed on Monday for bankruptcy protection, according to a company spokesperson. 
 Earlier a source told Reuters of the filing, as the company followed through with plans announced on Friday. (Reporting by Sabrina Lorenzi)